.TH JTUTIL-BRIGHT "1" "April 2026" "jtutil-bright manual" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jtutil-bright \- Generate an RGB brightness lookup table
.SH DESCRIPTION
Some arcade PCBs adjust the screen brightness with a resistor DAC
applied in parallel with each RGB DAC. This utility generates a LUT based on
the RGB DAC output impedance and the resistor unit used in the brightness DAC
.SS "Usage:"
.IP
jtutil bright [flags]
.SS "Flags:"
.TP
\fB\-b\fR, \fB\-\-bpp\fR int
bits per color component (at RGB DAC) (default 6)
.TP
\fB\-w\fR, \fB\-\-brw\fR int
bit width for brightness control (default 4)
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-dark\fR
Change color RDAC gain only, do not increase overall brightness
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
help for bright
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-ow\fR int
output bit width per color component (default 8)
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-rout\fR int
RGB DAC output impedance (assumed R2R) (default 600)
.TP
\fB\-u\fR, \fB\-\-runit\fR int
Unit resistor for the brightness DAC (assumed binary weighted) (default 250)
.SS "Global Flags:"
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Verbose
